Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) about Studying at the University of Nicosia
Where is the University of Nicosia located? The University of Nicosia is located in the capital city of Cyprus, Nicosia. Its main campus is situated in the heart of the city, providing students with easy access to amenities and cultural attractions.
What programs does the University of Nicosia offer? The university offers a wide range of undergraduate, postgraduate, and doctoral programs across various disciplines, including business, engineering, humanities, health sciences, and more. Additionally, it is renowned for its expertise in blockchain technology and cryptocurrency, offering specialized courses and a Master's program in Digital Currency.
Is there accommodation available for students? Yes, the University of Nicosia provides accommodation options for both local and international students. The university offers on-campus dormitories as well as off-campus housing assistance to help students find suitable accommodation.
What support services are available for students? The university offers comprehensive support services to ensure the well-being and success of its students. These include academic advising, career counseling, health and wellness programs, as well as various student clubs and organizations for extracurricular involvement.
